      <title>特朗普胜选导致全球降息预期严重受挫</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-11-06/trump-win-wreaks-havoc-with-rate-cut-expectations-around-world</link>
      <description><![CDATA[在唐纳德·特朗普 (Donald Trump) 强势重返美国总统大位后，世界各地的央行行长们都在判断，他们最担心的事情是否会成为现实。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-11-06/trump-win-wreaks-havoc-with-rate-cut-expectations-around-world</guid>
      <pubDate>Wed, 06 Nov 2024 16:03:58 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>拉尔夫·施洛斯坦表示，美国赤字将以惨淡收场</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/videos/2024-11-06/us-deficits-to-end-really-badly-ralph-schlosstein-says</link>
      <description><![CDATA[Evercore 名誉主席 Ralph Schlosstein 预计，美国政府将继续采取低税和过度支出的方式来解决赤字问题，直到最终结果可能是“从悬崖上开车而不是从山上滚下来”。 （来源：彭博社）]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/videos/2024-11-06/us-deficits-to-end-really-badly-ralph-schlosstein-says</guid>
      <pubDate>Wed, 06 Nov 2024 15:59:42 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>特鲁多试图安抚对特朗普回归感到“焦虑”的加拿大人</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-11-06/trudeau-tries-to-reassure-anxious-canadians-on-trump-s-return</link>
      <description><![CDATA[加拿大总理贾斯汀·特鲁多及其内阁部长试图平息人们对美国当选总统唐纳德·特朗普将对贸易造成严重破坏并可能摧毁加拿大出口导向型经济的担忧。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-11-06/trudeau-tries-to-reassure-anxious-canadians-on-trump-s-return</guid>
      <pubDate>Wed, 06 Nov 2024 15:55:15 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>对冲基金利用全员参与计划乘风破浪</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/videos/2024-11-06/hedge-funds-ride-red-wave-with-all-hands-on-deck-plans-video</link>
      <description><![CDATA[Hema Parmar 在“彭博未平仓合约”上表示，对冲基金为应对选举之夜的波动而增派人员，并进行对冲和采取避险头寸，直到当选总统唐纳德·特朗普的胜选形势明朗。（来源：彭博）]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/videos/2024-11-06/hedge-funds-ride-red-wave-with-all-hands-on-deck-plans-video</guid>
      <pubDate>Wed, 06 Nov 2024 15:29:17 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>特朗普胜选后欧洲债券卖家有望快速回归</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-11-06/europe-s-bond-sellers-set-for-brisk-return-after-trump-s-win</link>
      <description><![CDATA[欧洲债券销售可能最早于周四恢复，在唐纳德·特朗普赢得美国大选之前，企业债券发行暂停了一周，之后又重新回到了欧洲市场。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-11-06/europe-s-bond-sellers-set-for-brisk-return-after-trump-s-win</guid>
      <pubDate>Wed, 06 Nov 2024 15:26:53 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>阿斯利康称其现任和前任高管涉嫌中国调查</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-11-06/astra-says-current-former-executives-involved-in-china-probe</link>
      <description><![CDATA[阿斯利康公司表示，该公司两名现任和两名前任中国高管因涉嫌违反药品进口和数据隐私相关法律而接受调查。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-11-06/astra-says-current-former-executives-involved-in-china-probe</guid>
      <pubDate>Wed, 06 Nov 2024 14:11:43 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>玛莎百货警告称，里夫斯的预算将带来 1.2 亿英镑的税收和工资冲击</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-11-06/m-s-boosts-profit-despite-uncertain-outlook-after-reeves-budget</link>
      <description><![CDATA[玛莎百货集团表示，由于英国额外增加 1.2 亿英镑（1.55 亿美元）的工资和税款，该公司将“竭尽全力”避免将更高的成本转嫁给客户。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-11-06/m-s-boosts-profit-despite-uncertain-outlook-after-reeves-budget</guid>
      <pubDate>Wed, 06 Nov 2024 07:31:42 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>特朗普胜选对美国企业有利，信贷风险下降</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-11-06/credit-markets-send-some-of-their-most-bullish-signals-in-weeks</link>
      <description><![CDATA[唐纳德·特朗普赢得美国总统大选后，全球信贷市场出现反弹，表明投资者支持预期的减税政策，并且对这场被广泛认为基本打成平手的选举结果感到宽慰。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-11-06/credit-markets-send-some-of-their-most-bullish-signals-in-weeks</guid>
      <pubDate>Wed, 06 Nov 2024 05:47:57 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>特朗普关税风险冲击欧元、德国汽车股；可再生能源下跌</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-11-06/european-stock-futures-drop-over-tariff-worries-as-trump-leads</link>
      <description><![CDATA[由于唐纳德·特朗普的选举胜利加剧了人们对征收进口关税的担忧，欧元创下了四年多以来的最大单日跌幅，而汽车制造商等股票表现不佳。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-11-06/european-stock-futures-drop-over-tariff-worries-as-trump-leads</guid>
      <pubDate>Wed, 06 Nov 2024 05:44:21 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>特朗普胜选，标普 500 指数创历史新高：市场综述</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-11-05/stock-market-today-dow-s-p-live-updates</link>
      <description><![CDATA[股市创下历史新高，债券收益率飙升，美元有望创下 2020 年以来最好的一天，投资者正在关注唐纳德·特朗普重返白宫以及他的政策对市场的影响。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-11-05/stock-market-today-dow-s-p-live-updates</guid>
      <pubDate>Tue, 05 Nov 2024 23:05:37 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
